The paper discusses software release planning, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed approach involves mining user preferences, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of value-related feature dependencies, which could be modeled using machine learning algorithms (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the practicality of the proposed approach, which could be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it involves ensuring the security and reliability of software releases.
